s%20at%20Astronomer.%20He%20worked%20from%202019%20to%202023%20as%20an%20executive%20at%20Lacework%2C%20a%20cloud%20security%20company%20that%20was%20sold%20last%20year%20for%20an%20estimated%20%24200%20million%20to%20%24230%20million%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forrester.com%2Fblogs%2Ffortinet-acquires-lacework%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20Forrester%20Research%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20about%20two%20years%20before%20Lacework%2C%20he%20was%20the%20chief%20revenue%20officer%20at%20Cybereason%2C%20another%20software%20company.%20%3Cspan%3EThe%20company%20is%20privately%20held%20and%20raised%20a%20series%20H%20venture-capital%20round%20earlier%20this%20year%2C%20according%20to%20PitchBook%20data.%20Its%20head%20count%20and%20valuation%20grew%20while%20Byron%20worked%20there%2C%20but%20its%20head%20count%20has%20since%20declined%2C%20and%20its%20valuation%20fell%20significantly%20from%202022%20to%202023%2C%20per%20PitchBook.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20worked%20in%20the%20Boston%20tech%20scene%20for%20more%20than%20a%20decade.%20Earlier%20jobs%20included%20a%20sales%20executive%20role%20at%20Fuze%2C%20which%20sold%20communications%20and%20messaging%20software.%20It%20was%20sold%20in%202022%20for%20%24250%20million%2C%20and%20at%20Aveksa%2C%20which%20was%20acquired%20in%202013%20by%20RSA%2C%20an%20EMC%20subsidiary%2C%20for%20a%20reported%20price%20of%20%24225%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fastronomer-ceo-andy-byron-investigation-coldplay-kiss-cam-concert-video-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1752864967000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F687a82a83d5881a51c1d9b01%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fastronomer-ceo-andy-byron-investigation-coldplay-kiss-cam-concert-vid