workers%20who%20have%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20loved-up%20couple.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20don't%20know%20the%20story%20behind%20the%20Astronomer%20CEO%20and%20his%20Chief%20People%20Officer%20allegedly%20captured%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcoldplay-concert-ceo-kiss-cam-questions-why-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EColdplay's%20kiss-cam%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Still%2C%20the%20debacle%20has%20ignited%20a%20debate%20about%20workplace%20romances.%20Are%20they%20kosher%3F%20How%20%3Cem%3Eshould%3C%2Fem%3E%20you%20handle%20them%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFalling%20for%20a%20coworker%20is%20pretty%20common.%20Barack%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmichelle-obama-assistant-entrepreneur-tips-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EMichelle%20Obama%3C%2Fa%3E%20met%20as%20coworkers%20at%20a%20Chicago%20law%20firm.%20The%20%26quot%3BGood%20Morning%20America%26quot%3B%20hosts%20T.J.%20Holmes%20and%20Amy%20Robach%20left%20their%20spouses%20for%20each%20other.%20And%2C%20of%20course%2C%20there's%20the%20beloved%20Jim%20and%20Pam%20from%20%26quot%3BThe%20Office.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%202017%20Stanford%20study%20found%20one%20in%2010%20US%20couples%20met%20at%20work%2C%20while%20in%20a%20recent%20Forbes%20survey%20of%202%2C000%20working%20age%20Americans%2C%2060%25%20of%20people%20said%20they%20had%20experienced%20an%20office%20romance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20asked%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsigns-you-have-eldest-daughter-syndrome-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EAnnie%20Wright%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20licensed%20marriage%20and%20family%20therapist%2C%20if%20any%20of%20her%20clients%20have%20had%20an%20emotional%20or%20physical%20relationship%20with%20a%20coworker%20%E2%80%94%20including%20affairs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt'd%20be%20easier%20to%20mention%20the%20times%20it%20%3Cem%3Ehasn't%3C%2Fem%3E%20come%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20Wright%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BFalling%20for%2C%20or%20having%20an%20affair%20with%2C%20a%20coworker%20is%20so%20much%20more%20common%20than%20people%20tend%20to%20admit%20publicly.%20And%20I%20do%20have%20the%20privilege%20of%20being%20inside%20the%20hearts%20and%20minds%20of%20thousands%20of%20people%20at%20this%20point.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWright%20said%20workplace%20romances%20tend%20to%20start%20not%20with%20action%20but%20feelings%20%E2%80%94%20fantasies%2C%20quiet%20longings%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Ba%20mix%20of%20confusion%20and%20shame.%26quot%3B%20If%20her%20client%20is%20having%20an%20in-office%20affair%2C%20she%20often%20finds%20it%20isn't%20about%20the%20new%20relationship%20at%20all%3B%20it's%20about%20igniting%20something%20they've%20lost%20within%20themselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20the%20relationship%20isn't%20an%20affair%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fceo-not-allow-office-relationships-between-coworkers-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eromances%20between%20co-workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20be%20a%20headache%20not%20just%20for%20HR%2C%20but%20for%20colleagues%20who%20have%20to%20deal%20with%20their%20loved-up%20(or%20eventually%20broken-hearted)%20colleagues.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223348a514-07c9-411d-abc8-b187d34938b7%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWork%20is%20fertile%20ground%20for%20intimacy%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWorkplace%20romances%20have%20been%20happening%20for%20hundreds%20of%20years.%20There%20are%20accounts%20dating%20back%20to%201870%20of%20dalliances%20%E2%80%94%20then%20called%20%26quot%3Bbehaviors%20of%20no%20name%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20between%20men%20and%20women%20in%20white%20collar%20offices%2C%20documented%20by%20the%20historian%20Julie%20Berebitsky%2C%20author%20of%20%26quot%3BSex%20%26amp%3B%20The%20Office%3A%20A%20History%20of%20Gender%2C%20Power%2C%20and%20Desire.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20spend%20a%20%3Cem%3Elot%3C%2Fem%3E%20of%20time%20with%20our%20coworkers.%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20data%20shows%20that%20full-time%20workers%20average%207.6%20hours%20of%20work%20per%20day.%20If%20you're%20awake%20for%2016%20hours%20a%20day%2C%20that%20means%20over%20a%20third%20of%20your%20waking%20life%20is%20spent%20at%20work%20%E2%80%94%20in%20person%20or%20over%20Slack.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSimply%20seeing%20someone%20around%20frequently%20can%20make%20us%20feel%20more%20comfortable%20with%20and%20closer%20to%20them%2C%26quot%3B%20Vanessa%20Bohns%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20organizational%20behavior%20at%20Cornell%20University%2C%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20called%20the%20%26quot%3Bmere%20exposure%26quot%3B%20effect%2C%20Bohns%20said%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20more%20often%20you%20encounter%20someone%20or%20something%2C%20the%20more%20you%20report%20liking%20that%20thing%20or%20being%20attracted%20to%20that%20person.%26quot%3B%20Add%20that%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bpropinquity%20effect%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20human%20habit%20of%20forming%20relationships%20with%20people%20we%20are%20physically%20close%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOne%20famous%20study%20showed%20that%20people%20were%20more%20likely%20to%20develop%20close%20relationships%20with%20their%20next%20door%20neighbors%20than%20with%20people%20four%20doors%20down%2C%26quot%3B%20Bohns%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20makes%20sense%3A%20the%20more%20you're%20around%20someone%2C%20the%20more%20likely%20you%20are%20to%20build%20familiarity%2C%20learn%20their%20quirks%2C%20and%20see%20new%20sides%20to%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPlus%2C%20coworkers%20often%20share%20goals%2C%20stress%2C%20a%20routine%2C%20and%20their%20environment.%20They%20might%20rely%20on%20one%20another%20for%20reassurance%20or%20help%20with%20difficult%20tasks.%20Day-to-day%2C%20your%20coworkers%20can%20help%20you%20feel%20safe%2C%20successful%2C%20and%20in%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20%26quot%3Bare%20raw%20materials%20for%20emotional%20intimacy%2C%26quot%3B%20Wright%20said.%20That's%20why%2C%20while%20the%20workplace%20may%20feel%20like%20an%20inappropriate%20place%20for%20intimacy%2C%20in%20many%20ways%20it's%20natural.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe're%20dressing%20up%2C%20problem-solving%20together%2C%20or%20feeling%20seen%20or%20admired%20in%20ways%20that%20probably%20don't%20happen%20at%20home%20when%20you're%20being%20nagged%20to%20empty%20the%20dishwasher%20and%20shampoo%20your%20kids'%20hair%2C%26quot%3B%20Wright%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20almost%20intoxicating%20to%20be%20seen%20by%20someone%20in%20your%20work%20world%2C%20especially%20if%20you%20feel%20unseen%20or%20taken%20for%20granted%20elsewhere.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Jim%20and%20Pam%20from%20%26quot%3BThe%20Office%26quot%3B%20seated%20at%20a%20wedding.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F687a79b385e81483682e4813%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJim%20and%20Pam%20from%20%26quot%3BThe%20Office%2C%26quot%3B%20whose%20%26quot%3Bwill%20they%20won't%20they%26quot%3B%20storyline%20is%20central%20to%20the%20show.%3Cp%3E%3A%20Chris%20Haston%2FNBCU%20Photo%20Bank%2FNBCUniversal%20via%20Getty%20Images%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226475d463-bb38-4807-9411-0f922af12b51%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20midlife%20desire%20to%20feel%20alive%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20her%20clinical%20practice%2C%20Wright%20sees%20a%20%26quot%3Bnotable%20uptick%26quot%3B%20in%20workplace%20romances%20%26quot%3Bbetween%20the%20late%2030s%20and%20the%20early%2050s%2C%26quot%3B%20particularly%20among%20people%20in%20relationships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20a%20season%20where%20people%20begin%20to%20reevaluate%20everything%3A%20their%20marriage%2C%20their%20purpose%2C%20their%20sense%20of%20vitality%2C%26quot%3B%20Wright%20said.%20It's%20not%20about%20infidelity%2C%20per%20se%3B%20it's%20about%20identity.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you're%20married%20with%20kids%2C%20you%20and%20your%20partner%20have%20probably%20done%20some%20of%20the%20hardest%20and%20least%20exhilarating%20stuff%20together%20%E2%80%94%20budgeting%20for%20daycare%2C%20packing%20lunches%2C%20doing%20taxes%2C%20and%20working%20out%20who's%20washing%20the%20dishes%20this%20time.%20Wright%20calls%20this%20%26quot%3Bthe%20grind%20stage%26quot%3B%20of%20relationships.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20juicy%20connection%20with%20a%20coworker%20%26quot%3Bpierces%20the%20autopilot%26quot%3B%20of%20your%20domestic%20routine%2C%20possibly%20awakening%20long-buried%20parts%20of%20yourself%2C%20Wright%20said.%20Of%20course%2C%20if%20your%20relationship%20is%20already%20falling%20apart%2C%20a%20familiar%20face%20can%20also%20provide%20solace%20and%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhat%20they're%20usually%20trying%20to%20work%20out%20in%20the%20room%20with%20me%20isn't%20'should%20I%20pursue%20this%3F'%20but%20rather%20'what%20is%20this%20awakening%20of%20me%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%228304d1f6-fc44-4b32-b9da-f515217ae4db%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20it%20OK%20to%20have%20a%20workplace%20romance%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20reason%20everyone%20is%20sharing%20that%20kiss-cam%20clip.%20It's%20the%20same%20reason%20workplace%20romances%20are%20so%20common%20in%20pop%20culture%20%E2%80%94%20take%20%26quot%3BScandal%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BGrey's%20Anatomy%2C%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3BThe%20X-Files.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20really%20kind%20of%20disrupts%20the%20fantasy%20that%20work%20is%20separate%20from%20life%2C%26quot%3B%20Wright%20said.%20As%20outsiders%2C%20%26quot%3Bwe%20feel%20compelled%20to%20look%20at%20this%2C%20whether%20it's%20to%20condemn%20or%20to%20empathize%2C%20or%20honestly%2C%20because%20they're%20acting%20out%20a%20part%20of%20us%20that%20wishes%20we%20could%20do%20it.%20And%20we're%20wondering%2C%20well%2C%20what%20if%20I%20did%20that%3F%20It's%20a%20cultural%20lightning%20rod.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIs%20meeting%20someone%20at%20work%20inherently%20wrong%3F%20Not%20necessarily%2C%20but%20it's%20complicated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20research%20by%20the%20Society%20for%20Human%20Resource%20Management%2C%20workplace%20romances%20can%20increase%20the%20risk%20of%20awkward%20or%20hostile%20work%20environments%20(if%20it%20doesn't%20work%20out%2C%20seeing%20your%20ex%20%3Cem%3Eevery%20day%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20not%20exactly%20fun).%20There's%20also%20a%20risk%20other%20employees%20may%20file%20conflict-of-interest%20claims%2C%20Bohns%20said%20%E2%80%94%20you%20don't%20want%20other%20employees%20feeling%20like%20someone%20is%20getting%20special%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20big%20question%20to%20consider%20if%20you%20want%20to%20enter%20into%20an%20office%20romance%2C%20though%2C%20is%3A%20what's%20the%20power%20dynamic%3F%20Does%20one%20of%20the%20people%20in%20this%20liaison%20have%20control%20over%20the%20other's%20career%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20Bohns%20believes%20workplaces%20should%20be%20proactive%2C%20designing%20policies%20that%20protect%20the%20individuals%20involved%20and%20their%20professional%20colleagues%20from%20confusing%20dynamics.%20%26quot%3BPolicies%20that%20forbid%20workplace%20romance%20are%20bound%20to%20fail%2C%26quot%3B%20Bohns%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20find%20yourself%20in%20an%20office%20romance%2C%20Wright%20suggests%20taking%20a%20moment%20to%20think%20about%20what%20emotional%20need%20this%20is%20tapping%20into%20%E2%80%94%20particularly%20if%20you're%20already%20in%20a%20relationship.%20With%20clients%2C%20her%20primary%20goal%20is%20to%20strip%20out%20any%20shame%20or%20sheepishness%20so%20they%20can%20get%20to%20the%20root%20of%20what%20it%20is%20igniting.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESometimes%2C%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20spreadsheets%20and%20Slack%20messages%2C%20we%20don't%20just%20find%20connection%2C%20we%20find%20ourselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https